          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "To define a field’s area of effect, use the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnnode/1408026-position"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property of the node that contains the field and the field’s "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnphysicsfield/1388138-halfextent"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property. The center of the area of effect is the node’s position. The half-extent, a position vector in the local coordinate space of the node containing the field, marks one corner of a box, and the negative of the half-extent vector marks the opposite corner of the box. For example, if a node’s position is the vector "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "{2.0, 2.0, 2.0}"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and it contains a physics field whose half-extent is the vector "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "{0.5, 0.5, 0.5}"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", the field’s area of effect is the box extending from "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "1.5"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "2.5"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " along each axis of the scene’s coordinate system."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "By default, a field’s area of effect is the interior of this box shape. Use the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnphysicsfield/1388158-usesellipsoidalextent"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property to instead make the area of effect an ellipsoid bounded by this box. Use the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnphysicsfield/1388136-scope"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property to choose whether the area of effect is the interior or exterior of the box (or ellipsoid)."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The default half-extent is the vector "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "{INFINITY, INFINITY, INFINITY}"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", specifying that the field affects bodies located anywhere in the scene."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
